{
  "text": "where skip2(X, Y ) is the number of skip-bigram matches between X and Y (termed ROUGE-SU in [CITATION_1] ). For a candidate segment Y \u2208 E C , define R(Y ) = R(X max , Y ) and P (Y ) = P (X max , Y ) where X max = arg max X\u2208E R R(X, Y ).",
  "correct_citation": {
